criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Non-specific mechanical neck pain of at least 3 months of duration

          -  Between 18-60 years old

          -  At least one active trigger point in the upper trapezius muscle which referred pain
             reproduces the neck pain symptoms

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  whiplash injury;

          -  previous cervical or thoracic surgery;

          -  cervical radiculopathy or myelopathy;

          -  diagnosis of fibromyalgia syndrome;

          -  having undergone physical therapy in the previous 6 months;

          -  fear to needles
